features: 【Powerful Performance】 The 2023 HP Envy laptop offers strong performance, efficient power usage, and integrated graphics capabilities with its 12th generation Intel Core i7-1260P, a quad-core CPU with a base clock speed of 2.4 GHz. The CPU has Intel's Turbo Boost technology, which can increase its clock speed up to 4.7 GHz, making it a powerful processor for demanding tasks. With a TDP (thermal design power) of only 45 watts, the i7-1260p is a relatively low-power processor. This can be beneficial for systems where power consumption is a concern.

【Collaboration and Productivity】 The 17 inch Full HD (1920 x 1080) touchscreen features color accuracy for your creative projects and a wild viewing angle for teamwork or sharing video and online streaming with your friends and family. The 5MP camera with auto frame and privacy shutter with AI Noise Reduction provides you with a more clear video chat experience

【Full Size Keyboard】The number keypad can increase working productivity by allowing you to quickly and easily input numerical data. The laptop also provides a more comfortable typing experience to keeping your arms in a natural position while typing. This can help reduce strain on the hands and wrists for long term typing. The backlighting also improves the keyboard's visibility in low light and reduces eye strain for night typing

【Long Battery Life with Fast Charging 】The laptop has a 4-cell, 55 Wh Li-ion polymer battery with up to 9 hours of battery life, making it perfect for use from work to home. With comforts like an enlarged clickpad and HP Fast Charge technology to get back to it without waiting hours to recharge, approximately 50% in 45 minutes
【Windows 11 Pro and Other Supports】 The laptop comes with Windows 11 Pro pre-installed, giving you access to all the latest features and updates. The laptop is covered by 1 Year Warranty
body.description: Experience seamless connectivity with the HP Envy 17.3 Inch. Combine the creative power of your devices with HP Palette. With a large 17.3 Inch color-calibrated display, you get accurate colors. Plus, it has the Intel Processor to handle what you throw at it. Look and sound your best on video calls with a 5MP camera with Auto Frame and AI Noise Reduction A great value for business, personal use with casual gaming capacity Operating system Windows 11 Pro Processor and graphics Intel Core i7-1260P (up to 4.7 GHz, 18 MB L3 cache, 12 cores, 16 threads) + Intel Iris Xe Graphics Memory 64GB DDR4-3200 MHz RAM (2 x 32 GB) Expansion slots 1 multi-format SD media card reader Storage 2TB PCIe NVMe M.2 SSD External optical drive No DVD or CD Drive Display 17.3" diagonal, FHD (1920 x 1080), multitouch-enabled, IPS, edge-to-edge glass, micro-edge, 300 nits Screen-To-Body Ratio Screen-To-Body Ratio Webcam HP Wide Vision 720p HD camera with temporal noise reduction and integrated dual array digital microphones Audio Features Audio by Bang & Olufsen; Dual speakers; HP Audio Boost Keyboard Full-size, backlit, natural silver keyboard with numeric keypad External I/O Ports 2 Thunderbolt 4 with USB Type-C 40Gbps signaling rate (USB Power Delivery, DisplayPort 1.4, HP Sleep and Charge); 1 USB Type-A 10Gbps signaling rate (HP Sleep and Charge); 2 USB Type-A 10Gbps signaling rate; 1 HDMI 2.1; 1 headphone/microphone combo Wireless technology MediaTek Wi-Fi 6 MT7921 (2x2) and Bluetooth 5.3 wireless card Primary battery 4-cell, 55 Wh Li-ion polymer Battery Recharge Time
